(1, 1048585, 1, 5, '2017-01-16 16:11:55', '146.90.50.29', NULL, '"Matthew Byrne" <journal@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Test Author" <jnsamr-testauthor@deckofpandas.co.uk>', NULL, 'journal@nsamr.ac.uk, it@nsamr.ac.uk, jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk', '[JNSAMR] Submission Acknowledgement', 'Test Author:<br />\n<br />\nThank you for submitting the manuscript, &quot; Test paper 1&quot; to Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research. With the online journal management system that we are using, you will be able to track its progress through the editorial process by logging in to the journal web site:<br />\n<br />\nSubmission URL: http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/authorDashboard/submission/1<br />\nUsername: testauthor<br />\n<br />\nIf you have any questions, please contact me. Thank you for considering this journal as a venue for your work.<br />\n<br />\nMatthew Byrne<br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(2, 1048585, 1, 2, '2017-01-16 16:16:46', '146.90.50.29', NULL, '"Helen Jackson" <jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Test Reviewer" <jnsamr-testreviewer@deckofpandas.co.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] Article Review Request', '<p>Test Reviewer:<br> <br> I believe that you would serve as an excellent reviewer of the manuscript, " Test paper 1," which has been submitted to Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research. The submission\'s abstract is inserted below, and I hope that you will consider undertaking this important task for us.<br> <br> Please log into the journal web site by 2017-02-06 to indicate whether you will undertake the review or not, as well as to access the submission and to record your review and recommendation. The web site is <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr</a><br> <br> The review itself is due 2017-02-13.<br> <br> If you do not have your username and password for the journal\'s web site, you can use this link to reset your password (which will then be emailed to you along with your username). <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/login/lostPassword">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/login/lostPassword</a><br> <br> Submission URL: <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/reviewer/submission?submissionId=1">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/reviewer/submission?submissionId=1</a><br> <br> Thank you for considering this request.<br> <br> Helen Jackson<br>jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk<br> <br> " Test paper 1"<br> <br> Test paper 1 abstract</p><br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(3, 1048585, 1, 4, '2017-01-16 16:19:06', '146.90.50.29', 1073741829, '"Test Reviewer" <jnsamr-testreviewer@deckofpandas.co.uk>', '"Helen Jackson" <jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] Able to Review', 'Editors:<br />\n<br />\nI am able and willing to review the submission, &quot; Test paper 1,&quot; for Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research. Thank you for thinking of me, and I plan to have the review completed by its due date, 2017-02-13, if not before.<br />\n<br />\nTest Reviewer<br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(4, 1048585, 1, 2, '2017-01-16 16:21:13', '146.90.50.29', 805306369, '"Helen Jackson" <jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Test Author" <jnsamr-testauthor@deckofpandas.co.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] Editor Decision', '<p>Test Author:<br> <br> We have reached a decision regarding your submission to Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research, " Test paper 1".<br> <br> Our decision is to: Accept Submission<br> <br> Helen Jackson<br>jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk<br><br><br>------------------------------------------------------<br>Reviewer A:</p>\r\n<p>This is my review</p>\r\n<p><br>------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br></p><br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(5, 1048585, 1, 1, '2017-01-16 16:35:05', '146.90.50.29', NULL, '"JNSAMR Administration" <it@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Test Copy Editor" <jnsamr-testcopyeditor@deckofpandas.co.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] Copyediting Request', '<p>Test Copy Editor:<br> <br> I would ask that you undertake the copyediting of " Test paper 1" for Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research by following these steps.<br> 1. Click on the Submission URL below.<br> 2. Open any files available under Draft Files and do your copyediting, while adding any Copyediting Discussions as needed.<br> 3. Save copyedited file(s), and upload to Copyedited panel.<br> 4. Notify the Editor that all files have been prepared, and that the Production process may begin.<br> <br> Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research URL: <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr</a><br> Submission URL: <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/workflow/access/1">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/workflow/access/1</a><br> Username: testcopyeditor<br> <br> JNSAMR Administration<br>it@nsamr.ac.uk</p><br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(6, 1048585, 1, 2, '2017-01-16 16:37:43', '146.90.50.29', 805306369, '"Helen Mary Jackson" <jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Test Author" <jnsamr-testauthor@deckofpandas.co.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] Editor Decision', '<p>Test Author:<br> <br> The editing of your submission, " Test paper 1," is complete. We are now sending it to production.<br> <br> Submission URL: <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/authorDashboard/submission/1">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/authorDashboard/submission/1</a><br> <br> Helen Mary Jackson<br>jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk</p><br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(7, 1048585, 2, 9, '2017-01-19 22:44:58', '86.3.207.218', NULL, '"JNSAMR Administration" <journal@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Robert Michael Lundin" <lundinrm@nsamr.ac.uk>', NULL, 'journal@nsamr.ac.uk, it@nsamr.ac.uk', '[JNSAMR] Submission Acknowledgement', 'Robert Michael Lundin:<br />\n<br />\nThank you for submitting the manuscript, &quot; Developing a Digital Data Collection Platform for Wales&quot; to Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research. With the online journal management system that we are using, you will be able to track its progress through the editorial process by logging in to the journal web site:<br />\n<br />\nSubmission URL: http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/authorDashboard/submission/2<br />\nUsername: rmlundin<br />\n<br />\nIf you have any questions, please contact me. Thank you for considering this journal as a venue for your work.<br />\n<br />\nJNSAMR Administration<br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(8, 1048585, 4, 10, '2017-01-21 00:53:01', '147.188.254.245', NULL, '"JNSAMR Administration" <journal@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Godwin Tong" <GXT545@student.bham.ac.uk>', NULL, 'journal@nsamr.ac.uk, it@nsamr.ac.uk', '[JNSAMR] Submission Acknowledgement', 'Godwin Tong:<br />\n<br />\nThank you for submitting the manuscript, &quot; NSAMR4lyf&quot; to Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research. With the online journal management system that we are using, you will be able to track its progress through the editorial process by logging in to the journal web site:<br />\n<br />\nSubmission URL: http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/authorDashboard/submission/4<br />\nUsername: godwintong<br />\n<br />\nIf you have any questions, please contact me. Thank you for considering this journal as a venue for your work.<br />\n<br />\nJNSAMR Administration<br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(9, 1048585, 2, 1, '2017-01-22 14:43:32', '92.40.249.64', NULL, '"JNSAMR Administration" <it@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Helen Mary Jackson" <jacksonh@nsamr.ac.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] A message regarding Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research', '<p>Can we somehow add a reviewer to this...?</p><br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
(10, 1048585, 2, 1, '2017-01-22 14:48:24', '92.40.249.64', NULL, '"JNSAMR Administration" <it@nsamr.ac.uk>', '"Stephanie Rees" <reess@NSAMR.ac.uk>', NULL, NULL, '[JNSAMR] Article Review Request', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hey Steph and Akansha,</p>\r\n<p>This is a paper uploaded by Robert to test the journal process :) I\'ve set the paradigm to double-blind, so let me know if this is violated (by anything other than his name being in the file he uploaded!!!!)</p>\r\n<p>Please see if you can download the submission, then write some comments (literally "hello" will do) then upload at the link in this email and mark as review complete. Ask Helen if you need more info!</p>\r\n<p>H</p>\r\n<p>Stephanie Rees:<br> <br> I believe that you would serve as an excellent reviewer of the manuscript, " Developing a Digital Data Collection Platform for Wales," which has been submitted to Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research. The submission\'s abstract is inserted below, and I hope that you will consider undertaking this important task for us.<br> <br> Please log into the journal web site by 2017-02-12 to indicate whether you will undertake the review or not, as well as to access the submission and to record your review and recommendation. The web site is <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr</a><br> <br> The review itself is due 2017-02-19.<br> <br> If you do not have your username and password for the journal\'s web site, you can use this link to reset your password (which will then be emailed to you along with your username). <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/login/lostPassword">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/login/lostPassword</a><br> <br> Submission URL: <a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/reviewer/submission?submissionId=2">http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr/reviewer/submission?submissionId=2</a><br> <br> Thank you for considering this request.<br> <br> JNSAMR Administration<br>it@nsamr.ac.uk<br> <br> " Developing a Digital Data Collection Platform for Wales"<br> <br> Objective To develop a secure, efficient, and easy-to-use data collection platform to measure the prevalence of sepsis in Wales over 24 hours. Materials and Methods Open Data Kit was used on Android devices with Google App Engine and a digital data collection form. Results A total of 184 students participated in the study using 59 devices across 16 hospitals, 1198 datasets were submitted, and 97% of partici- pants found the Open Data Kit form easy to use. Discussion We successfully demonstrated that by combining a reliable Android device, a free open-source data collection framework, a scalable cloud-based server, and a team of 184 medical students, we can deliver a low-cost, highly reliable platform that requires little training or mainte- nance, providing results immediately on completion of data collection. Conclusion Our platform allowed us to measure, for the first time, the prevalence of sepsis in Wales over 24 hours.</p><br/><br/>\n________________________________________________________________________<br/>\n<a href="http://www.nsamr.ac.uk/journal/journal-machinery/ojs-3.0.1/index.php/jnsamr">Journal of the National Student Association for Medical Research</a>'),
